      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S is a superlative example of the 996.2 generation, featuring the wide-body chassis and all-wheel-drive architecture of the Turbo. The M96 3.6L flat-six engine features VarioCam Plus and delivers linear power through a precision 6-speed manual transaxle. The IMS bearing and rear main seal have been proactively retrofitted with LN Engineering components, and the cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat. The undercarriage is remarkably dry, showing no signs of fluid seepage, while the suspension retains factory-spec kinematics with Bilstein dampers. This is a turnkey, concours-ready specimen for the discerning purist seeking peak atmospheric performance.",
